# New England Cohort Dataset

This repository contains New England cohort dataset used in the following study:

Turesky TK, Escalante ES, Loh M, Gaab N.  
*Longitudinal trajectories of brain development from infancy to school age and their relationship to literacy development*  
https://doi.org/10.1101/2024.06.29.601366

For corresponding code, please see:  
https://github.com/TeddyTuresky/Longitudinal-Trajectories-Early-Brain-Development-Language/tree/main

For the dataset information please see:  
https://openneuro.org/datasets/ds006169/versions/1.0.7

---

All participants included in this repository had MR images from at least two timepoints that passed the QC standards for the manuscript referenced above. Any MR images for these participants from additional timepoints were also included regardless of whether they passed the QC standards.

Please note that session numbers and participant information correspond to the following developmental timepoints:

- **80 subjects, 192 scans in total**
- `ses-01` = infant, approximately 2–18 months old; data available for 62 participants.
- `ses-02` = toddler, approximately 16–26 months old; data available for 21 participants.
- `ses-03` = pre-reading, approximately 56–78 months old (≈4.6–6.5 years); data available for 51 participants.
- `ses-04` = beginning reading, approximately 73–101 months old (≈6–8.4 years); data available for 34 participants.
- `ses-05` = emergent reading, approximately 87–121 months old (≈7–10 years); data available for 24 participants.

